  serving size: 456
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/pan-fried-sea-bass-and-walnut-parsley-pesto-62fa0ea2278575d03208675d
author: Mimi Morley
servings: 2
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @walnuts{20} and @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped,
stalks and all). Transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Mix in the @hard Italian style cheese{25%g}(grated) and @olive oil{3%tbsp}
for the pesto (see pantry for amount), then season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}.

Stir well to combine, then set your walnut parsley pesto aside. TIP: Add a
little more olive oil if you'd prefer it to be more like a drizzle.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for amount). Season with @salt{}
and @ground black pepper{} and mix together.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}, then add them to the dressing. Stir
together, then set aside - you'll add the rocket later.

Put the @plain flour{2%tbsp} on a #plate{} and season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}.

Pat the @sea bass fillets{2} dry with some #kitchen paper{}, then lay onto the
plate of seasoned flour. Turn the fish so it's evenly coated all over.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

When the potatoes have 5 mins left, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large
#frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, carefully place your sea bass into the pan, skin-side down. Cook
for ~{3-4%minutes} before turning over and cooking for ~{2-3%minutes} on the other
side.

> To get crispy skin on the fish, don't move it around when it's cooking
> skin-side down. The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the heat.

When everything is ready, add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the bowl of tomatoes
and toss together.

Serve the sea bass with the roast potatoes and salad alongside.

Spoon your walnut parsley pesto over the fish to finish. Enjoy!